# Skill Tournaments - API Test Requests
#
# Open this file in VS Code with the "REST Client" extension installed
# (humao.rest-client in the extensions marketplace).
#
# Each request is separated by "###". Click "Send Request" above any block
# to execute it. Responses appear in a pane on the right.
#
# Start the TypeScript system first:  docker compose up --build  (gateway on :3000)
# Start the JavaScript system first:  docker compose up --build  (gateway on :3001)
#
# Change @host below to switch between the two.

@host = http://localhost:3000

### 1. Join a tournament - Alice joins an FPS ranked tournament
POST {{host}}/tournaments/join
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "playerId": "player-1",
  "gameType": "fps",
  "tournamentType": "ranked",
  "entryFee": 10
}

### 2. Join the same tournament - Bob joins the same one (finds existing open tournament)
POST {{host}}/tournaments/join
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "playerId": "player-2",
  "gameType": "fps",
  "tournamentType": "ranked",
  "entryFee": 10
}

### 3. Duplicate join - Alice tries to join the same tournament again (expect 409)
POST {{host}}/tournaments/join
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "playerId": "player-1",
  "gameType": "fps",
  "tournamentType": "ranked",
  "entryFee": 10
}

### 4. Unknown player - expect 404
POST {{host}}/tournaments/join
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "playerId": "player-999",
  "gameType": "fps",
  "tournamentType": "ranked",
  "entryFee": 10
}

### 5. Validation error - missing required field (expect 400)
POST {{host}}/tournaments/join
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "playerId": "player-1",
  "gameType": "fps"
}

### 6. Alice joins a second, different tournament
POST {{host}}/tournaments/join
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "playerId": "player-1",
  "gameType": "rts",
  "tournamentType": "casual",
  "entryFee": 5
}

### 7. Charlie joins a third tournament type
POST {{host}}/tournaments/join
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "playerId": "player-3",
  "gameType": "moba",
  "tournamentType": "open",
  "entryFee": 0
}

### 8. Get all tournaments for Alice (player-1) - should show fps/ranked and rts/casual
GET {{host}}/tournaments/players/player-1

### 9. Get all tournaments for Bob (player-2) - should show fps/ranked
GET {{host}}/tournaments/players/player-2

### 10. Get tournaments for a player with no entries
GET {{host}}/tournaments/players/player-4
